# Personal Preferences
#
# This file customizes Claude's behavior for YOU specifically.
# It is gitignored and never shared with your team.
#
# To activate: rename this file to CLAUDE.local.md
#   mv CLAUDE.local.md.example CLAUDE.local.md

## Communication Style
- Be terse. Skip preamble and summaries unless I ask.
- Don't explain code you wrote unless I ask "why."
- When I say "fix it," apply the fix directly — don't list options.

## Local Environment
- Dev server runs on port 3000
- Database runs on localhost:5432
- My project root is ~/code/myproject
- I use zsh on macOS

## Workflow Preferences
- Always run tests after editing code, don't wait for reminders.
- Commit with --no-verify when I say "quick commit."
- When reviewing, focus on logic errors over style — the linter catches style.
- I prefer small, focused commits over large ones.
